<div class="body" id="fhbody-63441915">
	

	
		
		<div id="text-63441915" class="p">
			
		 	
				<a href="/~sciencehabit">sciencehabit (1205606)</a> writes <i>Even when the sea looks clean, its <a href="http://news.sciencemag.org/chemistry/2014/08/sea-polluted-paint-dust">surface can be flecked with tiny fragments of paint and fiberglass</a>. That's the finding from a <a href="http://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/es501757s">study that looked for plastic pollution in the uppermost millimeter of ocean</a>. The microscopic fragments come from the decks and hulls of boats, and they could pose a threat to zooplankton, an important part of the marine food web.</i>
		 	
